verbose_text: The overexpression of ROCK1 in LPS treated HCECs strengthened the inflammation by further inducing the activities of TLR4 mediated NF-kappaB and ERK signaling, indicating a promoting role of ROCK1 in the onset of bacterial keratitis.
evidence: ROCK1 in LPS-treated HCECs strengthened the inflammation by further inducing the activities of TLR4-mediated NF-kappaB and ERK
